Total: 42 + 3 Magi   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is a generic weave deck for the most part. I play creatures, get stupid bonuses when I get attacked, and hope my opponent doesn&#39;t play an Ormagon w/Warrior&#39;s Boots. The only real exception is that nearly every other weave deck out there makes use of that wretched horn/trug combo for nearly infinite trugs... I&#39;m trying to stay away from that. The idea is that the main offense is the Lascinth, based on his ability to survive being attacked.<br>
